Key Match Events: Jason Holder took 4 wickets for 7 runs, dismissing England for 103.
Brandon King scored an unbeaten 55 off 49 balls.
West Indies won by 9 wickets, chasing down 104 in 17.1 overs.
Sheldon Cottrell took 2 wickets for 30 runs.
Akeal Hosein claimed 1 wicket for 16 runs.
Post-Match Reflections: Jason Holder emphasized the challenge of being consistent and repeating the team's performance.
Eoin Morgan discussed the need to balance risk and reward and hoped to play better in the upcoming matches.
Kieron Pollard praised the team's clinical display and the batsmen's adjustment to the pitch conditions.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Kensington Oval in Barbados.
England had dominated the previous series in the Caribbean in March 2019.
